                           <q xml:lang="en"><p><span unicode="" style="line-height: 115%; font-size: 10pt;">Fol. 83ra-b:</span><span unicode="" style="line-height: 115%; font-size: 10pt;"> This book of </span><span style="line-height: 115%; font-size: 10pt;">&#704;A&#705;mad&#228; m&#477;s&#7789;ir is of &#7717;al&#228;qa T&#228;sfay&#228; [of] K<sup>w</sup>&#228;k<sup>w</sup>&#228;lo, who is G&#228;br&#228; S&#477;llase. {His wife is &#7722;irut&#228; S&#477;llase} and his father M&#228;zg&#228;b&#228; S&#477;llase, and his children Kin&#228; S&#477;llase, &#7716;abt&#228; S&#477;llase, &#7722;ayl&#228; S&#477;llase, &#704;Am&#228;t&#228; S&#477;llase, W&#228;l&#228;tt&#228; S&#477;llase, &#7788;&#477;b&#228;b&#228; S&#477;llase, L&#477;&#7717;k<sup>w</sup>&#477;t&#228; S&#477;llase, S&#477;mr&#228;t&#228; S&#477;llase, and his mother W&#228;l&#228;tt&#228; &#704;&#398;gzi&#704;, and her mother W&#228;l&#228;tt&#228; Maryam, and her sister &#705;Am&#228;t&#228; &#7778;&#477;yon, and her daughter W&#228;l&#228;tt&#228; B&#477;rhan, and his brother G&#228;br&#228; Giyorgis that is &#7723;al&#228;qa &#704;Abbay. May the one who stole it or erased it or took it by force without the permission of the owner be excommunicated by the authority of Peter and Paul like Arius and Macedonius. </span></p></q>
                           <p>The note contains a tämäläs-sign, in the shape of two perpendicular lines, indicating where the omission, written above, belongs: fol. 83ra l.8.</p>
